{
  "stem": "19690.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 422.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But anyway, we moved in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And it got tighter and tighter as far as being able to escape.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And finally, my uncle and aunt decided they were going to go on to Frankfurt, where he was more familiar with the area and had friends that could possibly hide him.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Well, he got to Frankfurt and the first thing he did was run into a Nazi barricade and he was arrested and the car was taken into custody.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "My aunt stayed with some friends there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We later find out that Uncle Heinz, who was the uncle from Stuttgart-- his wife's name, my mother's older sister, was Elsa, and their son, Martin-- that Heinz had been arrested in this small town.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "He never went to Dachau, but he was regularly bludgeoned in this small jail in this small town by jailers or whoever wanted to have a go at him.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And he would have probably been better off in Dachau than he was there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "My Uncle Ernst, who also lived in Speyer with his wife, Ruth, and their daughter, Liesel, he also wound up in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Ruth and Liesel-- Ruth's mother lived in Italy and the two of them were there visiting.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "When they found out what was happening, they stayed extra time and didn't come home right away.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And so they were not exposed to all this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We stayed at my aunt's for about two and a half weeks and then we were told that all of the furniture had to be moved out of the house in Speyer.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So my mother made arrangements with a moving company to do that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And then about five days later, they told us, you can now come back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "So all the furniture had to be brought back.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
